I guess any bad opinion that is anti-reso is better than a valid one to him. \<br>
- Incorrect.  You need to be a little more thorough in your readings before making a sweeping comment like that.  In fact I have agreed with things stated by Reso personnel (seeing as you choose to focus on that particular guild) just as I have disagreed.  <br>
<br>
You don't have the slightest clue what goes on between our guilds and individual members.  I group with Reso members, I joke with Reso members, I buff Reso members and receive in kind (thx Nothsa for the rez last night).<br>
<br>
I took a satirical jab at one of the catalysts for the thread and view.  I have just as much right to make a statement, visual or verbal, as Coriolis does to brand all these people as &quot;dishonorable&quot;, or as Qixx does to speak his mind, or as you do to disagree with any of the above.<br>
<br>
But I'll give you this challenge Neehygh:  find a thread where I tell someone to &quot;fuck off&quot; or I call them a name, or make a broad sweeping, predjudicial judgement on a group of people exhibiting some tertiary in-game trait (i.e. having some gear they obtained while on Stormhammer).  If you want to single me out for a) posting a suitably funny picture or b) giving a guildmate a punch on the shoulder for something that made me laugh...then you better look deeper and see what has precipitated a few of these threads - personal attacks, intolerance, jealousy and even more ugly stuff.  And I'll tell you up front, it wasn't me that started them (other than my pic of Coin and Rollen, which was in response to two threads filled with profanity and name-calling).<br>
<br>
&quot;Don't know ya, but starting to feel like I do.&quot;<br>
-  Sure, form your own opinion, but do your homework if you're going to make a sharp statement.  But talking like that, you just turned your own statement against yourself:<br>
<br>
I guess any statement by Kurley is bad, even a valid one.  <br>
<br>
Seems to be where you're going with your statement.  If you don't like satire or cynicism, them maybe the soapbox isn't for you.  F&amp;F and Reso will clash, as will their members and it will come up again and again.  And frankly, people won't really change their views:  Coriolis has strong opinions and he's going to state them, Gore is proficient with emoticons and he's going to use them, Coinfist likes to repudiate people with strong language, and I like politically inspired satirical pictures and I'm going to keep making them...<br>
